## Highlight active domain in L1 navbar

**Context:** When a domain is open and the user is on `/domain/`, the Domain
entry in the top navbar had no visual distinction from inactive items. This
made it hard to see which "section" of the app was active at a glance.

**Changes:**
1. `src/front/static/global/js/navbar.js` — extended `initSubnavActiveState()`
   to also add `.active` to `#domainL1Link` when `window.location.pathname`
   starts with `/domain/`.
2. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` — added `#domainL1Link.active` rule:
   darker background (`--db-primary-dark`), white text, rounded pill, bold;
   plus a hover variant using `--db-primary-darker`.

**Modified files:**
- `src/front/static/global/js/navbar.js`
- `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`

**Test result:** visual only — no unit tests impacted.
